LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 112
BY JUDICIARY AND RULES COMMITTEE
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 STATING FINDINGS OF THE LEGISLATURE AND REJECTING CERTAIN RULES OF THE IDAHO
3 DEPARTMENT OF LANDS RELATING TO RULES GOVERNING GRAZING, FARMING, CON-
4 SERVATION, NONCOMMERCIAL RECREATION, AND COMMUNICATION SITE LEASES.
5 Be It Resolved by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 WHEREAS, the Legislature is vested with authority to reject executive
7 agency rules under the provisions of Section 67-5291, Idaho Code, in the
8 event that the Legislature finds that the rules are not consistent with leg-
9 islative intent; and
10 WHEREAS, it is the finding of the Legislature that certain rules of the
11 Idaho Department of Lands relating to Rules Governing Grazing, Farming, Con-
12 servation, Noncommercial Recreation, and Communication Site Leases are not
13 consistent with legislative intent because any state grazing lease may be
14 canceled with only six months' notice and should therefore be rejected.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED by the members of the First Regular
16 Session of the Sixty-eighth Idaho Legislature, the Senate and the House of
17 Representatives concurring therein, that the final rule contained in IDAPA
18 20.03.14, Section 050., Subsection 02., relating to Rules Governing Graz-
19 ing, Farming, Conservation, Noncommercial Recreation, and Communication
20 Site Leases, Rules of the Idaho Department of Lands, only, be, and the same
21 is hereby rejected and declared null, void, and of no force and effect on and
22 after July 1, 2025.

